record_data.record_title: Revenue Requirement for Reactive Supply and Voltage Control
record_data.record_plain_text:
AMERICAN MUNICIPAL POWER, INC. SPECIFICATION OF REVENUE REQUIREMENT
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (ATSI Transmission Zone - Fremont Energy Center)
American Municipal Power, Inc. ("AMP") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system from AMP's 94.84% ownership share of the Fremont Energy Center (the "FEC"). The FEC is located within the American Transmission Systems, Incorporated ("ATSI") transmission pricing zone of PJM. This Specification sets forth AMP's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM from the FEC, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. AMP's annual and monthly revenue requirements for this service are set forth below. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the product of 12 times the monthly revenue requirement specified below.
ANNUAL AND MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENTS: Annual Revenue Requirement is $1,866,564.00 Monthly Revenue Requirement is $155,547.00
EFFECTIVE DATE: April 1, 2013 pursuant to letter order issued April 25, 2013 in FERC Docket No. EL13-55-000
